## 🧪 Integration Test Cases

### Test Group A: Arithmetic + Logic

```rust
#[test]
fn test_integrated_arithmetic_logic() {
    // (10 + 20) > 25 ? YES
    // PUSH 10, PUSH 20, ADD, PUSH 25, LT, NOT
    // Expected: 1 (true)
}

#[test]
fn test_integrated_complex_expression() {
    // ((5 * 3) - 10) == 5 ? YES
    // PUSH 5, PUSH 3, MUL, PUSH 10, SUB, PUSH 5, EQ
    // Expected: 1
}

#[test]
fn test_integrated_modulo_and_compare() {
    // (17 % 5) < 3 ? NO
    // PUSH 17, PUSH 5, MOD, PUSH 3, LT
    // Expected: 0 (false)
}
```

### Test Group B: Control Flow + Memory

```rust
#[test]
fn test_integrated_loop_with_variables() {
    // Loop 5 times, store result in variable
    // PUSH 0, STORE 0
    // LOOP: LOAD 0, INCR, STORE 0, LOOP
    // Expected: counter = 5 at end
}

#[test]
fn test_integrated_if_else_with_variables() {
    // if (x > 10) { x = 100 } else { x = 50 }
    // LOAD 0, PUSH 10, LT, JIT(else), PUSH 100, JMP(end)
    // else: PUSH 50, end: STORE 0
    // Expected: x = 100 or 50 based on condition
}

#[test]
fn test_integrated_nested_calls() {
    // Function calls with local variables
    // CALL(outer), HALT
    // outer: CALL(inner), LOAD 0, RET
    // inner: PUSH 42, STORE 0, RET
    // Expected: 42
}
```

### Test Group C: Array Operations

```rust
#[test]
fn test_integrated_array_sum() {
    // Create array [1, 2, 3, 4, 5], sum elements
    // ARRALLOC(5), PUSH 1, PUSH 0, ARRSET, ...
    // PUSH 0, ARRGET, PUSH 1, ARRGET, ADD, ...
    // Expected: 15
}

#[test]
fn test_integrated_array_search() {
    // Create array, find index of value
    // ARRALLOC(4), populate, loop to find value
    // Expected: correct index
}

#[test]
fn test_integrated_array_double_loop() {
    // Nested loops with array
    // ARRALLOC(3), outer loop counts down, inner loop increments
    // Expected: correct iteration count
}
```

### Test Group D: String Operations

```rust
#[test]
fn test_integrated_string_ascii_values() {
    // Create string "ABC", verify ASCII values
    // STRALLOC(3), PUSH 65, PUSH 0, STRSET, ...
    // PUSH 0, STRGET -> 65, PUSH 1, STRGET -> 66, etc.
    // Expected: 65, 66, 67
}

#[test]
fn test_integrated_string_with_loops() {
    // Loop through string, double each character
    // STRALLOC(3), loop to read/compute/store
    // Expected: doubled ASCII values
}

#[test]
fn test_integrated_array_of_strings() {
    // Multiple string allocations, access sequentially
    // STRALLOC, STRALLOC, STRALLOC, set/get from each
    // Expected: correct heap management
}
```

